{"parse":{"title":"computer","pageid":2798,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Computer|compùter}}\n==English==\n{{swp}}\n{{swp|+ (occupation)}}\n{{swp|[[Mental calculator|Mental calculator (human +)]]}}\n{{multiple images\n|direction=vertical\n|image1=Human_computers_-_Jet_Propulsion_Laboratory_employees.jpg|caption1=Human '''computers''' at NASA's {{w|Jet Propulsion Laboratory}} (1955).\n|image2=Science museum 025 adjusted.jpg|caption2=An [[electronic computer|electronic '''computer''']] (circa early 1980s).\n}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*pewH-}}\n{{etymon|en|id=device|:af|compute<id:calculate>|-er<id:agent noun>|text=+}} {{doublet|en|cantore|counter|kontor}}. The sense referring to people first appears c. 1613 in the works of the poet {{w|Richard Brathwait}}. The sense referring to a machine first appears c. 1897 in the magazine ''{{w|Engineering (magazine)|Engineering}}''.\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|compooter}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjuːtə/|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjʉwtə/|a=SSB}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-uk-computer.ogg|a=Southern England}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpɪʊtə/|a=Wales}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjʉːtə/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{a|en|rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjutɚ/|[kəmˈpjuɾɚ]|a=GA}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-computer.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjʉtəɾ/|a=Scotland}}\n** {{IPA|en|/kəmˈpjʉtəɹ/|a=Northern Ireland}}\n* {{rhymes|en|uːtə(ɹ)|s=3}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|com|put|er}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q68}} A [[programmable]] electronic [[device]] that performs [[mathematical]] [[calculation]]s and [[logical]] [[operation]]s, especially one that can [[process]], [[store]] and [[retrieve]] large amounts of [[data]] very quickly; now especially, a small one for personal or home use employed for manipulating text or graphics, accessing the Internet, or playing games or media. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|'puter<qq:informal clipping>|box<qq:slang>|;|Thesaurus:computer}}\n#: {{hyper|en|machine<id:Q11019>|device#Noun<qq:sometimes {{glossary|elliptically}} synonymous>}}\n#: {{hypo|en|desktop|laptop|PC|personal computer|portable computer|mainframe|supercomputer}}\n#: {{mer|en|processor|microprocessor|CPU}}\n#: {{cot|en|calculator<id:machine for calculating><!--usually construed as coordinate, sometimes as hyponymous-->}}\n#: {{ux|en|I spend around 6 hours a day at the '''computer'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|As well as saving the photos on my '''computer''', I have them backed up on a [[USB]] drive.}}\n#: {{ux|en|David is a '''computer''' expert.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Janet works at the '''computer''' store.}}\n# {{senseid|en|person who computes}} {{lb|en|originally|;|now|rare|;|chiefly|historical}} A [[person]] [[employ]]ed to perform [[computation]]s; one who [[compute]]s. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|computator|mental calculator|human calculator}}<!-- {{w|Mental calculator}} -->\n#: {{hypo|en|computress}}\n## {{lb|en|by restriction|chiefly|historical}} A [[male]] [[computer]].\n##: {{coord|en|computress|q1=female}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1613|author=w:Richard Brathwait|title=The Yong Mans Gleanings|text=I haue read the truest '''computer''' of Times, and the best Arithmetician that euer breathed, and he reduceth thy dayes into a short number: The daies of Man are threescore and ten.|url=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A00514.0001.001?rgn=main;view=fulltext|page=1|pageurl=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A00514.0001.001/10?vid=16329}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1674|author=<!-- Anonymous -->|chapter=To the Guardian-Angel|title=Reflexions upon the Devotions of the Roman Church|location=London|publisher=w:Richard Royston|page=419|pageurl=https://archive.org/stream/reflexionsuponde00patr#page/419|passage=By which manner of ſpeaking, this Propheteſs, who is ſo exact a Computer, would have us, I ſuppoſe, to conclude, that it would be a great miſtake to think that the number of Angels was either 9, or 11 for one of Men.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1927|author=w:J. B. S. Haldane|title=Possible Worlds and Other Essays|location=London|publisher=w:Chatto & Windus|page=173|text=Only a few years ago Mr. Powers, an American '''computer''', disproved a hypothesis about [[prime number]]s which had held the field for more than 250 years.|url=https://searchworks.stanford.edu/view/8708294}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|title=Numerical Computing with IEEE Floating Point Arithmetic|author=Michael L. overton|page=1|publisher=SIAM|text=During World War II, scientific laboratories had rooms full of people doing different parts of a complicated calculation using pencil and paper, slide rules, and mechanical calculators. At that time, the word '''''computer''''' referred to a person, and those group calculations may be viewed as the early steps of parallel computing.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2003|author=w:Bill Bryson|title=A Short History of Nearly Everything|publisher=BCA|page=116|text=One Harvard '''computer''', Annie Jump Cannon, used her repetitive acquaintance with the stars to devise a system of stellar classifications so practical that it is still in use today.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* In modern everyday use, [[smartphone]]s and [[tablet]]s are not typically referred to as ''computers'', except in certain ways, such as \"we now live in an age when almost everyone can have a computer in their pocket every day\".\n\n====Quotations====\n* {{see citations|en}}\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|computor}} {{q|obsolete}} \n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{sense|programmable electronic device}} [[device|electronic device]], [[machine]]\n\n====Hyponyms====\n{{col4|en|title=programmable electronic device\n|analog computer|analogue computer|deskside computer|midrange computer|pedestal computer|server computer|zombie computer\n|appliance computer\n|biocomputer,biological computer\n|briefcase computer\n|classical computer\n|desktop computer\n|digital computer\n|dive computer|trip computer\n|domino computer\n|electromechanical computer,electro-mechanical computer\n|home computer\n|hybrid computer\n|laptop computer|electronic computer\n|microcomputer\n|minicomputer\n|notebook computer\n|personal computer\n|pocket computer\n|quantum computer\n|supercomputer|reservoir computer|spatial computer\n|tablet computer\n|ternary computer\n|wearable computer|gaming computer\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en| computer-controlled timing|mecomtronics|precomputers\n|computerate|computer paper|computer illiteracy|computer-mediated communication\n|computerese| anticomputer|compucondria|compunications|compusex|computer illiteracy|computeracy|computerbased|computercide|computerdom|computeresque|computerette|computerful|Computergate|computerholic|computerisation|computerist|computeristic|computeritis|computerland|computerless|computerlore|computernik|computerologist|computerology|computerphile|computerphobe|computerphobia|computerphobic|computerphone|computerspeak|computerware|computery|computronium|cyclocomputer|hypercomputer|intercomputer|macrocomputer|maxicomputer|memcomputer|multicomputer|neurocomputer|noncomputer|precomputer|telecomputer|transputer\n|computerise\n|computerism|computer illiterate\n|computerize\n|computerlike\n|computress\n|computer-aided design\n|computer architecture\n|computer-based,computer-based teaching\n|computer chess\n|computer chip\n|computer code|computer engineer\n|computer conferencing|computer-aided translation\n|computer core\n|computer dating\n|computer engineering\n|computer game\n|computer graphics\n|computer lab\n|computer language\n|[[computer literacy]], {{nowrap|[[computer-literate]]/}}{{nowrap|[[computer literate]]}}\n|computer model\n|computer network\n|computer person\n|computer processor\n|[[computer program]] ([[computer programme]]), [[computer programming]]\n|computer says no\n|computer science,computer scientist\n|computer security\n|computer shop\n|computer simulation\n|computer system|computer programmer\n|computer technician\n|computer typesetting\n|computer virus\n|computer vision,computer vision syndrome\n|human-computer interaction\n|phoneputer\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col4|en\n|compute\n|computation\n|computing\n|computus\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{col-top|2|desc}}\n* {{desc|sq|kompjuter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|am|ኮምፒዩተር|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ar|كَمْبْيُوتَر|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|az|kompüter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|be|камп'ю́тар|кампу́тар|камп'ю́тэр}}\n* {{desc|bn|কম্পিউটার|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bg|компю́тър|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|my|ကွန်ပျူတာ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nl|computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|et|kompuuter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ka|კომპიუტერი|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|el|κομπιούτερ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hi|कंप्यूटर|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|id|komputer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|コンピューター|tr=konpyūtā|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|km|កុំព្យូទ័រ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ko|컴퓨터|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ky|компьютер|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lo|ຄອມພິວເຕີ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lv|kompjūters|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lt|kompiuteris|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lb|Computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mk|компју́тер|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|komputer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ml|കമ്പ്യൂട്ടർ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mt|kompjuter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kmr|kompûter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|or|କମ୍ପ୍ୟୁଟର|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fa|کامپیوتر|tr=kâmpyutar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pih|kompyuuta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|komputer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ro|computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|rm|computer|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|ru|компью́тер|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|rue|компю́тер|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gd|coimpiutair|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sh|-|bor=1}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{l|sh|компјутер}}\n*: {{desc|sh|kompjuter|sclang=1}}\n* {{desc|sw|kompyuta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|kompiyuter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|tg|компютер|компутар}}\n* {{desc|ta|கம்ப்யூட்டர்|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|te|కంప్యూటర్|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|th|คอมพิวเตอร์|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tpi|kompyuta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tk|kompýuter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tr|kompüter|bor=1}} {{q|obsolete}}\n* {{desc|uk|комп'ю́тер|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ur|کمپیوٹر|tr=kampyūṭar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ug|كومپيۇتېر|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|xh|ikhompyutha|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sah|көмпүүтэр|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yi|קאָמפּיוטער|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zu|ikhompyutha|bor=1}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|programmable electronic device}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|rekenaar}}\n* Albanian: {{tt|sq|kompjuter|m}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ኮምፒዩተር|?}}\n* Amis: {{tt|ami|kampiwta}}, {{tt|ami|tingnaw}}\n* Apache:\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|bésh eʼléhí}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|حَاسُوب|m}}, {{tt|ar|حَاسِب|m}}, {{tt+|ar|كَمْبْيُوتَر|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|كمبيوتر|m|tr=kombeyūtar}}, {{t|arz|كومبيوتر|m|tr=kombeyūtar}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|كمبيوتر|tr=kambyūtar, kampyūtar}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܚܲܫܘܼܒ݂ܵܐ|m}}, {{tt|aii|ܟܘܿܡܦܝܘܼܬܸܪ|m}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|համակարգիչ}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|কম্পিউটাৰ}}, {{tt|as|পৰিকলন যন্ত্ৰ}}, {{tt|as|সংগণক যন্ত্ৰ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|computadora|f}}, {{tt|ast|ordenador|m}}\n* Atayal: {{tt|tay|tennaw}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|kompüter}}, {{t+|az|bilgisayar}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|ordenagailu}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|камп'ю́тар|m}}, {{tt|be|кампу́тар|m}}, {{tt|be|камп'ю́тэр|m}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|কম্পিউটার}}, {{tt+|bn|গণকযন্ত্র}}, {{t|bn|গণনাযন্ত্র}}, {{t|bn|সংগনক}}\n* Bouyei: {{tt|pcc|dianqnaoj}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|urzhiataer|m}}, {{tt+|br|kompoder|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|компю́тър|m}}\n* Bunun: {{tt|bnn|tinnau}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ကွန်ပျူတာ}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{tt|rue|компю́тер|m}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|ordinador|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|kompyuter}}, {{tt|ceb|dagitok}}, {{tt|ceb|dagitabyan}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎠᏍᏆᎾᎪᏗᏍᎩ}}\n* Cheyenne: {{tt|chy|tséohketoetanóto}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|電腦}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|дянно}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{tt|cdo|電腦}}\n*: Hakka: {{tt|hak|電腦|tr=thien-nó}}, {{tt|hak|計算機|tr=kie-son-kî, ki-son-kî}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|電腦|tr=tiān-náu}}, {{tt|nan-hbl|計算機|tr=kè-sǹg-ki}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|電腦}}, {{tt+|cmn|計算機}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|電腦}}\n* Cornish: {{tt|kw|jynn-amontya|m}}\n* Corsican: {{t|co|cumputatore|m}}, {{t|co|ordinatore|m}}\n* Cree: {{tt|cr|ᒪᓯᓇᑕᑲᐣ ᒋᑲᐢᑌᐸᔨᒋᑲᓂᐢ}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|bilgisayar}}, {{t|crh|kompyuter}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|počítač|m}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|regnemaskine|c}}, {{tt+|da|computer|c}}, {{tt|da|datamat|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|computer|m}}, {{tt+|nl|rekenaar|m}}\n* Dzongkha: {{tt|dz|གློག་རིག}}\n* Erzya: {{tt|myv|содамопель}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|komputilo}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|arvuti}}, {{tt|et|kompuuter}} {{q|obsolete}}, {{tt+|et|raal}} {{q|obsolete}}\n* Faroese: {{tt+|fo|telda|f}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|tietokone}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|ordinateur|m}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{tt+|fy|kompjûter|m}}\n* Fula:\n*: Adlam: {{tt|ff|𞤸𞤭𞥅𞤧𞤮𞤪𞤺𞤢𞤤}}\n*: Latin: {{tt|ff|hiisorgal}}\n* Gagauz: {{t|gag|kompyuter}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|ordenador|m}}, {{tt+|gl|computador|m}}, {{tt+|gl|computadora|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|კომპიუტერი}}, {{tt|ka|გამომთვლელი მანქანა}}, {{tt|ka|პერსონალური კომპიუტერი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Computer|m}}, {{tt+|de|Rechner|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|υπολογιστής|m}}, {{tt+|el|κομπιούτερ|n}}\n* Greenlandic: {{tt|kl|qarasaasiaq}}, {{tt|kl|computeri}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{tt-check|gug|mohendaha}}\n* Guiqiong: {{tt|gqi|diɐnnə}}\n* Gujarati: {{tt|gu|સંગણક|m}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{tt|ht|òdinatè}}, {{tt|ht|konpitè}}\n* Hausa: {{tt+|ha|na'ura}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|lolouila}}, {{tt|haw|kamepuila}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מַחְשֵׁב|m|tr=makhshév}}\n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|संगणक|m}}, {{tt+|hi|कंप्यूटर|m}}, {{tt|hi|अभिकलित्र|m}}\n* Hmong:\n*: White Hmong: {{tt|mww|koos pis tawj}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|számítógép}}, {{q|dated}} {{tt+|hu|komputer}}\n* Hunsrik: {{tt|hrx|Komputatoer|m}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|tölva|f}}, {{tt|is|rafheili|m}} {{q|obsolete}}, {{tt|is|rafreiknir|m}} {{q|obsolete}}, {{tt|is|rafeindareiknir|m}} {{q|obsolete}}\n* Igbo: {{tt|ig|orunotu}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|komputer}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt+|ia|computator}}\n* Inuktitut: {{tt|iu|ᖃᕋᓴᐅᔭᖅ}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|ríomhaire|m}}\n* Isoko: {{tt|iso|ụkrọkrịịmị}}, {{tt|iso|ịkọputa}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|calcolatore|m}}, {{tt+|it|computer|m}}, {{tt+|it|elaboratore|m}}, {{tt+|it|ordinatore|m}} {{qualifier|Switzerland}}, {{tt+|it|computatore|m}}, {{tt+|it|computiere|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|コンピュータ|tr=kompyūta}}, {{tt+|ja|コンピューター|tr=kompyūtā}}, {{tt+|ja|電脳|tr=でんのう, dennō}} {{q|rare}}, {{tt+|ja|電子計算機|tr=でんしけいさんき, denshi keisanki}} {{q|rare}}, {{tt+|ja|電算|tr=でんさん, densan}}\n* Jeju: {{tt|jje|콤퓨타}}\n* Kabyle: {{tt+|kab|aselkim|m}}\n* Kalmyk: {{tt|xal|тооцлур}}\n* Kamba: {{tt|kam|kompiuta|?}}\n* Kanakanabu: {{tt|xnb|tennau}}\n* Kannada: {{tt+|kn|ಗಣಕಯಂತ್ರ}}\n* Kaurna: {{tt|zku|mukarntu}}\n* Kavalan: {{tt|ckv|tiannaw}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt+|kk|компьютер}}, {{tt|kk|білгісаяр}}\n* Khmer: {{tt+|km|កុំព្យូទ័រ|tr=kompyuutoa}}, {{tt-check|km|គណិតូបករណ៍|tr=kuənnetoopkɑɑ}}\n* Kikuyu: {{tt|ki|mompyuta|?}}, {{tt|ki|kompyuta|?}}\n* Kis: {{tt|kis|ekompyuta}}\n* Kongo: {{tt|kg|ludinatelo|?}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|컴퓨터}} {{q|South Korea}}, {{tt+|ko|전자계산기(電子計算機)}}, {{tt+|ko|콤퓨터}} {{q|North Korea}}, {{tt+|ko|뗀노}} {{q|Yanbian}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt+|ckb|کۆمپیوتەر}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|kompûter}}, {{tt+|kmr|bilgîsayar}}, {{tt+|kmr|xêvjimêr}}, {{tt+|kmr|kombers}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|компьютер}}, {{tt|ky|эсепкер}}\n* Ladino: {{tt|lad|majhshev|?}}, {{tt|lad|contador|m}}\n* Lao: {{tt+|lo|ຄອມພິວເຕີ}}, {{tt|lo|ເຄື່ອງຄຳນວນ}}, {{tt|lo|ສະໝອງກົນ}}\n* Latgalian: {{tt|ltg|dators|?}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|computātōrium|n}}, {{tt+|la|computātrum|n}}, {{tt|la|ōrdinātrum|n}}\n* Latvian: {{tt+|lv|dators|m}}, {{tt+|lv|kompjūters|m}}, {{t|lv|skaitļotājs|m}}\n* Limburgish: {{t+|li|computer|m}}\n* Lingala: {{tt|ln|esálela|?}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|kompiuteris|m}}\n* Low German:\n*: German Low German: {{tt+|nds-de|Computer|m}}, {{tt|nds-de|Reekner|m}}, {{tt|nds-de|Rääkner|m}}\n* Lü: {{tt|khb|ᦶᦎᧃᧈᦓᧁ}}\n* Luhya: {{tt|luy|ekompyuta|?}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{tt|lb|Computer|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|сметач|m}}, {{tt+|mk|компју́тер|m}}\n* Malagasy: {{tt+|mg|solosaina}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|komputer}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt|ml|സംഗണകം}}, {{tt+|ml|ഗണിനി}}, {{tt+|ml|കമ്പ്യൂട്ടർ}}, {{tt|ml|എണ്ണിനി}}, {{tt|ml|ഗണനി}}, {{tt|ml|ഗണനിക}}, {{tt|ml|സംഗണകയന്ത്രം}}, {{tt|ml|സംഗണനി}}, {{tt|ml|സകലകലായന്ത്രം}}, {{tt|ml|സങ്കണകയന്ത്രം}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|kompjuter|m}}\n* Manx: {{tt|gv|co-earrooder|m}}\n* Māori: {{tt+|mi|rorohiko}}, {{t|mi|rorouira}}\n* Marathi: {{tt+|mr|संगणक|m}}\n* Meru: {{tt|mer|kompyuta|?}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|компьютер}}, {{tt+|mn|цахим тооцоолуур}}\n* Nahuatl: {{tt|nah|chīuhpōhualhuaztli}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|béésh bee akʼeʼelchíhí tʼáá bí nitsékeesígíí}}, {{tt|nv|béésh nitsékeesí}}\n* Ndebele:\n*: Southern Ndebele: {{tt|nr|umtjhiningqondo|?}}\n* Nepali: {{tt+|ne|कम्प्युटर}}, {{tt|ne|सुसाङ्ख्य|tr=susānkhya}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|compiuteu|m}}\n* Northern Sotho: {{tt|nso|khomphutha|?}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|datamaskin|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|datamaskin|m|f}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|ordinator|m}}\n* Odia: {{tt|or|କମ୍ପ୍ୟୁଟର}}\n* Ojibwe: {{tt|oj|mazinaabikiwebinigan}}\n* Paiwan: {{tt|pwn|tinnaw}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|компютер|m}}\n* Pashto: {{tt|ps|کمپيوټر|m|tr=kampyūṭar}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|کَمْپْیُوتَر}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|رایانِه|tr=râyâne}}, {{tt|fa-ira|کامْپْیوتِر|tr=kâmpyuter}}\n* Pitcairn-Norfolk: {{tt|pih|kompyuuta}}, {{tt|pih|kohmpyuuta}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|komputer|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|computador|m}}, {{t|pt|calculador|m}}\n* Punjabi: {{tt|pa|ਸੰਗਣਕ|?}}\n* Puyuma: {{tt|pyu|tinnaw}}\n* Quechua: {{tt|qu|antañiqiq}}\n* Rarotongan: {{t|rar|rorouira}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|computer|n}}, {{tt+|ro|calculator|n}}, {{t+|ro|ordinator|n}}\n* Romansh: {{tt|rm|computer|m}}, {{tt|rm|calculader|m}}\n* Rukai: {{tt|dru|tingnau}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|компью́тер|tr=kompʹjútɛr|m}}, {{tt+|ru|ЭВМ|f}}\n* Rwanda-Rundi: {{tt+|rw|mudasobwa|?}}\n* Saaroa: {{tt|sxr|tinnau}}\n* Saisiyat: {{tt|xsy|tiyaenaw}}\n* Sakizaya: {{tt|szy|tingnaw}}\n* Sami:\n*: Inari Sami: {{tt|smn|tiättur}}\n*: Lu