}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|bilgisayar}}, {{t+|tr|kompüter}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|kompýuter}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|комп'ю́тер|m}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|pënaelìntàmahikàn}}\n* Urdu: {{tt+|ur|کَمْپْیُوٹَر|m|tr=kampyūṭar}}, {{tt+|ur|حاسِب|m|tr=hāsib}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt+|ug|كومپيۇتېر}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|kompyuter}}\n* Venda: {{tt|ve|khomphiyutha|?}}\n* Veps: {{tt|vep|tedomašin}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|máy vi tính}}, {{tt+|vi|máy điện toán}}, {{tt+|vi|máy tính}}, {{t+|vi|máy tính điện tử}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|nünöm}}\n* Võro: {{tt|vro|puutri}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|cyfrifiadur|m}}\n* Wolof: {{tt|wo|nosukaay}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|ikhompyutha|9|10}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|көмпүүтэр}}\n* Yami: {{tt|tao|tiannaw}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|קאָמפּיוטער|m}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|kọ̀ǹpútà}}, {{tt|yo|kọ̀m̀pútà}} {{qualifier|nonstandard}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|naaqsuun}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|dennauj}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|Isicikizi}}, {{tt|zu|ikhompyutha|5|6}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|person}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|مُحَاسِب|m}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܡܲܚܫܒ݂ܵܢܵܐ|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|изчисли́тел|m}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|computador|m}}, {{tt|ca|calculador|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt|cmn|計算者|tr=jìsuànzhě}}, {{tt+|cmn|計算員|tr=jìsuànyuán}}\n* Czech: {{tt|cs|sčítač|m}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|rekenaar|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|komputisto}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|arvutaja}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|laskija}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|λογιστής|m}}, {{tt+|el|λογίστρια|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|fejszámoló}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|計算手|tr=けいさんしゅ, keisanshu}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пресметувач|m}}\n* Manx: {{tt|gv|co-earrooder|m}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|countour}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|rīmere|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|rachmistrz|m}}, {{t+|pl|kalkulator|m}}, {{t|pl|kalkulatorka|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|computador|m}}, {{tt+|pt|calculista|m|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|вычисли́тель|m}}, {{tt+|ru|вычисли́тельница|f}}, {{tt+|ru|расчётчик|m}}, {{tt+|ru|расчётчица|f}}, {{tt+|ru|счётчик|m}}, {{tt+|ru|счётчица|f}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|cuntaturi|m}}, {{t|scn|raggiuneri|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|computador|m}}, {{tt+|es|calculador|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|mänsklig beräknare|c}}, {{tt|sv|mänsklig räknare|c}}, {{tt+|sv|räknare|c}}, {{tt|sv|beräknare|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|taga-kompyut}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Sindhi: {{t+check|sd|ڳڻپيوڪر|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}} {{tlb|en|rare|nonstandard}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To use a computer.\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|author=Roxanne Coyle|title=B'days|newsgroup=bit.listserv.words-l|url=https://groups.google.com/g/bit.listserv.words-l/c/YZZPcqA45A4/m/B2jD3TcdxroJ|date=31 December 1995|passage=Cool he was '''computering''', though. My dad, who is only in his 60's (mom too) thinks he is too busy to get connected to the internet. Oh well. More bandwidth for the rest of us, huh?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The World According to Mimi Smartypants|location=London|publisher=[[w:HarperCollins|HarperCollinsEntertainment]]|year=2004|page=36|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/worldaccordingto0000smar/page/36/mode/1up|isbn=0-007-17342-3|passage=I don't know if you have the same violent mood-swing issues that I do, but I was bustling around the house feeling very useful and good, and then I was sitting here '''computering''' for a while, and suddenly it was like a giant butterfly net scooped me up and threw me into an old mayonnaise jar, {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Alyssa Shelasky|title=What I Discovered When I Outsourced My Back Pain|work=w:New York Magazine|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131010214/https://nymag.com/strategist/article/best-back-pain-remedies.html|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:New York Media|date=16 May 2017|issn=0028-7369|oclc=1760010|passage=I'm constantly '''computering''', schlepping, stressing, and hauling ass like the rest of us. We are New Yorkers.}}\n#* {{quote-av|en|episode=Finding Mr. Right|title=[[w:Harley Quinn (TV series)|Harley Quinn]]|season=1|number=4|actor=w:Kaley Cuoco|role=w:Harley Quinn|date=20 December 2019|text=Yeah, you saw what he could do when he flips out. I mean, how am I going to say no to that? Plus, he does '''computer''' good.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To send via computer.\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Marcel Montecino|title=The Crosskiller|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Arbor House; w:William Morrow|year=1988|page=351|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/crosskiller00mont/page/351/mode/1up|isbn=0-877-95908-0|passage=They had immediately '''computered''' the description out to the scores of law enforcement agencies in Southern California.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Will Kingdom|title=Mean Spirit|location=London{{nb...}}|publisher=w:Bantam Press|year=2001|page=428|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/meanspirit0000king/page/428/mode/1up|isbn=0-593-04896-2|passage='Nah. It was him hated it more than me. Fish out of water. Cops watching every move he makes. Memos about him '''computered''' to every nick in the land. He was too innocent for this hi-tech world, Bobby. Would've been back inside in no time at all.'}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To transfer onto a computer; to [[computerize#Verb|computerize]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|quotee=Benny L. Kass|title=U.S. Government Information Policies and Practices: Administration and Operation of the Freedom of Information Act|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[w:United States Government Publishing Office|U.S. Government Printing Office]]|date=20 March 1972|page=1425|pageurl=https://books.google.ca/books?id=2MxEAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA1425|passage=I know there are storage warehouses in New York and Virginia and all over the place, St. Louis, and many other places, that keep these things. I think this is a very fertile area for this committee, and perhaps '''computering''' it, or microfilm preservation, or things of that sort.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=H. Ahrendt; N. Clauer; J. C. Hunziker; K. Weber|chapter=Migration of Folding and Metamorphism in the Rheinische Schiefergebirge Deduced from K-Ar and Rb-Sr Age Determinations|title=Intracontinental Fold Belts: Case Studies in the Variscan Belt of Europe and the Damara Belt in Namibia|location=Berlin{{nb...}}|publisher=w:Springer-Verlag|year=1983|page=336|pageurl=https://books.google.ca/books?id=_43sCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA336|doi=10.1007/978-3-642-69124-9_15|isbn=978-3-642-69126-3|passage=Our sincere thanks are due to Antje Reuter, Jens Adam and Uwe Horstmann for '''computering''' the manuscript and Ralph Phillips and Kirsten Techmer for proof reading it.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Shimon Applebaum|chapter=Foreward|title=Judaea in Hellenistic and Roman Times|location=Leiden{{nb...}}|publisher=w:E. J. Brill|year=1988|page=unnumbered|pageurl=https://books.google.ca/books?id=ScwUAAAAIAAJ&pg=PP11|isbn=978-9-004-08821-4|passage=It is also a pleasure to recommend the skill of Irit Markan who carried out the work of ''''computering'''' the text, and of Ivor Ludlam who bore the labour of proof reading—both the English and the Greek.}}\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|author=Burr|title=MFW has been milked dry|newsgroup=misc.fitness.weights|url=https://groups.google.com/g/misc.fitness.weights/c/-knNAzpf_nI/m/y2QvxUSrPGgJ|date=21 November 2010|passage=I have 30 years worth of logs some place and they have been '''computered''' the last few years and the last few years I think I have posted them to the sites I hang out on.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n|computering<t:gerund>\n|computered<t:adjective>\n}}\n\n===See also===\n{{col4|en\n|chip\n|data processing\n|desktop\n|hardware\n|laptop\n|mainframe\n|microprocessor\n}}\n\n===References===\n* [https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A00514.0001.001/1:4?rgn=div1;view=fulltext Richard Brathwaite, Of the Mortalite of Man, 1613]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20221018142359/https://www.oed.com/oed2/00045995 computer – Oxford English Dictionary, second edition (1989).]\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:commons}}\n\n{{C|en|Computing|Mathematicians}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|da|en|computer}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|[kʰʌmˈpʰj̊uːd̥ɐ]|[kʰʌmˈpʰj̊uːtˢɐ]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|e}}\n\n# {{l|en|computer}} (machine)\n\n====Declension====\n{{da-decl|en|e|ne}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|nl|kompjoeter||eye dialect|humorous}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/kɔmˈpjutər/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-computer.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|com|pu|ter}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|utər|s=3}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ubor|nl|en|computer}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-s|+}}\n\n# {{l|en|computer}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|nl\n|boordcomputer\n|computeranimatie\n|computeren\n|computergame\n|computeringenieur\n|computermuis\n|computernerd\n|computerprogramma\n|computerscherm\n|computerspel\n|computertoets\n|computervirus\n|computervredebreuk\n|computer zegt nee\n|fietscomputer\n|microcomputer\n|nanocomputer\n|spelcomputer\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|tri|konpëjutë|bor=1}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|computeren||bare-verb}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|fr|id=compute|:lbor|la:computāre<id:computō, āre-form>}}\n{{bor+|fr|la|computō|computāre|to compute, sum up}}. See also the doublets {{doublet|fr|compter|conter|notext=1}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lepticed7-computer.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Toulouse>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-computer (verbe).wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-computer (nom commun).wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-computer.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n* {{fr-homophones-er|comput}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|archaic|rare}} to [[compute]]\n#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1802|author=w:François-René de Chateaubriand|title=Génie du christianisme\n|passage=Quant aux ères, ici on compte par l'année de la création, là par olympiade, par la fondation de Rome, par la naissance de Jésus-Christ, par l'époque d'Eusèbe, par celle des Séleucides, celle de Nabonassar, celle des martyrs. Les Turcs ont leur hégire, les Persans leur yezdegerdic. '''On compute''' encore par les éres julienne, grégorienne, ibérienne et actienne.|t=As the eras, here they compute by the year of the creation, there by olympiads, by the foundation of Rome, by the birth of Christ, by the epoch of Eusebius, by that of Seleucids, of Nabonassar, of the Martyrs. The Turks have their hegira, the Persians their yezdegerdie. The Julian, Gregorian, Iberian and Actian eras, '''are''' also '''employed in computation'''.}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{fr-conj-auto}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|fr|supputer}}\n* {{l|fr|compter}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|compteur}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|it|en|computer}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|compiùter<r:DiPI><audio:It-un computer.ogg><hyph:com.pù.ter>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# {{l|en|computer}} (calculating device)\n#: {{syn|it|calcolatore|elaboratore}}\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|computō||1|s|pres|pasv|subj}}\n\n==Limburgish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|li}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|li|/kɔmˈpjutəʀ/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|li|noun|g=m|plural|computers|diminutive|computerke}}\n\n# {{lb|li|computing}} {{l|en|computer}} {{q|machine}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|li|computerlès}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:li:D'n Dictionair}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|ro|en|computer}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|ro|LL-Q7913 (ron)-Andreea Teodoraa-computer.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|n|computere}}\n\n# {{l|en|computer}}\n#: {{syn|ro|calculator|ordinator}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|ro|computa}}\n\n==Romansh==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|rm|en|computer}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{rm-noun|m}}\n\n# [[#English|computer]]\n#: {{syn|rm|calculater}}\n\n{{C|rm|Computing}}"}}